AGI - The United Nations Agency for Palestinian Refugees (UNWRA) announced the suspension of food distribution to Rafah, for supply and security problems in that southern Gaza city, the scene of fighting between Israel and the Palestinian Islamist movement Hamas. "Food distribution in Rafah is currently suspended due to lack of supplies and insecurity," UNWRA said on social network X. "After the beginning of the Israeli military operation, on May 7, "the UNRWA distribution center and the PAM storage in Rafah are inaccessible," he said.
&nbsp;
Even arrivals through the floating pier made by the United States have been blocked for two days. According to the Guardian, the project of using that passage for aid by sea is also at risk because of the lack of guarantees for humanitarian agencies by Israel.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Meanwhile, the Cnn citing three sources reveals that the last attempt to reach a peace agreement in the Middle East has failed because of an incorrectness of Egyptian mediators, who have changed the terms of the agreement without warning the other participants in the ongoing talks in Cairo.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Israel had already given its ok to an agreement on the truce that provided for the release of Israeli hostages and Palestinian prisoners and a ceasefire of a few weeks. Just the change decided by the Egyptian intelligence, according to the US broadcaster, made the agreement naufragare on 6 May last. The conditions submitted to Hamas were different from those that had agreed on the other negotiators, Qatar and the United States, who together with Israel felt "untrained", blowing up the deal. Particularly embarrassed and angry about this incorrect operation would have been CIA director Bill Burns, according to CNN.&nbsp;

