&nbsp;
It is since 1914 that the very popular medium, present in the photos and memories of all those who have visited at least once the metropolis on the Bosphorus, is a symbol of the city, much more for its appearance to say a little of time and for the sound of the bell, necessary to make room between the crowd, than for the short itinerary of just a kilometer and a half.
<div </div As from another era, the four&nbsp;tram&nbsp;rossi will continue to change and widen with traditional wooden finishes and period seats, among the crowd that 24 hours a day characterizes the most famous pedestrian artery in Istanbul. Only novelty, the cameras instead of the rearview mirrors and the 'green' batteries that will allow him to travel 150 km with only one charge. For the rest the &nbsp;tram&nbsp;rosso will continue to appear in the photos of tourists and arouse the astonishment of those who will see it behind the crowd, a monovagon that seems to come from a distant age, testimony of an eternal city and yet in continuous change. &nbsp;
